Singer Wizkid has decided not to be put down by his loss at the 64th Grammys as he goes on to improve his shooting skills. Star boy, who received nominations for the ‘Best Global Music Performance’ and ‘Best Global Music Album’ categories but lost out, was spotted in an indoor shooting range in a recent viral video.   Davido excited as EFCC frees Cubana Chief Priest     DJ Cuppy begs God for husband     Davido’s aide Isreal DMW proposes to girlfriend   In the video shared by the “Essence” global hitmaker on his Insta story, he was seen holding an assault rifle with headphones to block out the sounds as he aimed and shot at a human-shaped paper target. Though Wizkid has since deleted his shooting video, he left the photo that showed the bullets holes on different parts of the paper target after his practice time.